					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-7060165#post-3924600</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-7060165/scp-4222#post-3924600</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 24 Aug 2018 15:41:11 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Crossync</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3607892</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I think it might be a reference to SCP-2719, which is the metaphysical concept of either entering or becoming something (made unique by becoming or entering the concept itself). To me, the reference to that metaphysical attribute makes it more clear that the bank doesn't have a purely literal presence - it's implied by the half-formed hellscape inside the tuna, but I like the reinforcement using Foundation-centric language.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
